-- Absa, BHP, Metorex, Steinhoff May Move: South Africa Equity Market Preview
-- Carli Lourens
-- 2010-09-07T06:08:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-06/absa-metorex-and-steinhoff-may-move-south-african-equity-market-preview.html

          
          
             The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close.  
 The  FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index  gained 37.7, or 0.1
percent, to 27,980.60 in Johannesburg.  
 Absa Group Ltd.  (ASA SJ): The country’s largest mortgage
lender appointed  Garth Griffin  as chairman from Oct. 1 to
succeed  Dave Brink . Absa advanced 15 cents, or 0.1 percent, to
126.15 rand.  
 Afgri Ltd.  (AFR SJ): Wheat futures climbed to a three-week
high on speculation that the U.S. Department of Agriculture may
pare its estimate of global inventories for a fourth time,
signaling tighter supply. The December-delivery contract rose as
much as 1 percent to $7.485 a bushel in Chicago, the highest
since Aug. 13. Afgri, which handles about a quarter of South
Africa’s grain, gained 2 cents, or 0.3 percent, to 6.40 rand.  
 BHP Billiton Ltd.  (BIL SJ): The world’s largest mining
company asked to cooperate with Zhongchuan International Mining
Holding Ltd. to jointly develop a potash mine in Canada, China
Business News reported, citing Chairman  Sun Ximing . BHP shares
fell 3.38 rand, or 1.6 percent, to 210.79 rand.  
 Metorex Ltd.  (MTX SJ): The copper producer posted a profit
of 640 million rand ($88.2 million) for the 12 months through
June, compared with a loss of 1.54 billion rand a year earlier,
and said production of the metal jumped 60 percent. Shares in
the company rose 4 cents, or 1.1 percent, to 3.64 rand.  
 Steinhoff International Holdings Ltd.  (SHF SJ): The
furniture maker releases earnings for the year through June.
Shares in Steinhoff gained 14 cents, or 0.7 percent, to 19.24
rand.  
